            <div style="font-size: 130%; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px">
            MANAGING DIRECTOR'S GREETINGS
            </div>
            
            I am pleased to inform you that our company will be celebrating its 20th anniversary in 2006. The past twenty years have, as a whole, been a time of steady growth, whereas during the most recent years we have faced fast growth. For instance, in 2005 our sales were up by 35 % compared to the previous year. The number of our staff members has also grown from five in 2002 to nine in 2005. Our customer base has outnumbered its original number series so that we have had to start new series!

            <br><br>
            Our customers are at the heart of our day-to-day business. Based on our principles of independence and partnership, we are committed to building long-term trust based relationships with our customers and business partners. It is our conviction that these are the foundations not only of continuity and reliability, but also of exceptional product quality and service excellence.
            <br><br>
            All this is thanks firstly, to our customers and secondly, to our staff. Ruslania’s employees have shown a unique team spirit in meeting growing professional challenges. The staff with a down-to-work attitude, respect for the customers and professionalism has made this fast growth possible.
            
            <br><br>
            Today we sell Russian books and periodicals to a diverse audience on all the four continents. The pace of growth has demanded serious investments, hard work and much learning. In my opinion, we have managed to serve our foreign customers well in most cases and, in some cases, even exceeded their expectations. It is a fine feeling when a customer comes back to you with a “spasibo” – i.e. a word of gratitude.
            
            <br><br>
            The selection of products in our book store is continuously expanding. We also begin the sale of completely new product lines. We wish to be a company that meets the customer demand, even if the required product is currently out of our stock. Here I wish to express my gratitude to all our splendid suppliers in Russia, Finland and elsewhere. I feel great when I can promise a customer that an item he orders on Tuesday will be available in our store on Thursday! We also take pride in the fact that we deliver some Russian newspapers with only a one day after the date of publishing. We have been constructing this supply chain from the very first days of the company and now finally all the pieces of the puzzle seem to fit to their places.
            
            <br><br>
            As a Finnish family-owned company we can be truly proud of our accomplishments. We can undoubtedly say that we are one of the leading dealers of Russian books in Europe and one of the leading dealers of Russian sheet music worldwide! Some of the best ideas were brought about by our customers. That is why we value customer feedback and proposals. Some expectations of our customers may have felt impossible to fulfill but eventually, many of these “missions impossible” have turned into everyday business routines. For instance, this was the case with the Garmin electronic maps (our most recent product line), of which we had no earlier experience whatsoever. But as a customer insisted on us to start selling them, we now supply these maps in Finland and worldwide.
            <br><br><br>
            </td>
            <td class="maintxt" valign="top" style="padding: 10px; border-left: 1px solid #CFD8DE;">
